    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Orthorhombic mineral of the native element sulfur, having symbol S and atomic number 16.  It is found abundantly in volcanic regions, occurring as a brittle crystalline solid, widely distributed in combination with metals and other substances. It has been used as molten to create small objects and as a gap-filler, for bleaching wood pulp, straw, wool, silk, felt, and linen, for vulcanizing rubber, for making gunpowder, and in the manufacture of sulfa drugs, insecticides, plastic, enamels, and dyes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
